','Legal, HR, and Accounting','Management only','IT security','B','HR, Legal, and Accounting regularly accept external documents, making them prime phishing targets.',2),(103,27,'Why is privilege escalation needed after initial exploitation?','To delete log files','Initial access is usually low-privilege (e.g., www-data)','To install antivirus','To update the system','B','Exploits typically give low-privilege access; escalation is needed for full control.',1),(104,27,'What does chmod u+s do?','Makes file hidden','Sets the SUID bit','Removes write permission','Encrypts the file','B','chmod u+s sets the SUID bit, making the file run with the owners privileges.',2),(105,29,'How do you find SUID files on Linux?','ls -la /','find / -perm -4000','grep -r suid /','cat /etc/suid','B','find / -perm -4000 locates files with the SUID bit set.',1),(106,29,'How can sudo find be exploited for privesc?','By finding hidden files','sudo find /etc -exec sh -i \\; spawns a root shell','By searching for passwords','It cannot be exploited','B','The -exec flag in find can execute arbitrary commands ‚Äî with sudo, those run as root.',2),(107,30,'What is the highest privilege level on Windows?','Administrator','Power User','SYSTEM','Domain Admin','C','SYSTEM has unrestricted access and is reserved for OS services ‚Äî higher than Administrator.',1),(108,30,'Where might stored credentials be found?','In the registry only','In unattend.xml and sysprep files','In the hosts file','In the firewall rules','B','Credentials are often left in deployment files like unattend.xml, encoded in Base64.',2);
